  <sect1>
    <title>Introduction</title>

    <para xml:id="first-para">The <code>xtpxlib-xdoc</code> component (GitHub: <code>https://github.com/eriksiegel/xtpxlib-xdoc</code>) uses
      DocBook&#160;5 as its target vocabulary. Within this DocBook source there can be so-called <emphasis>xdoc extensions</emphasis> that will be
      converted into "pure" DocBook by pipelines in this component. This article documents how this works (<xref linkend="sect-xdoc-mechanism"
      />).</para>
    <para>Specific xdoc transformations can come from the <code>xtpxlib-xdoc</code> component, for instance the conversion of XML element descriptions
        (<xref linkend="sect-builtin-xdoc"/>). They can also be specifically written in XProc (1.0) or XSLT (<xref linkend="sect-own-xdoc"/>).</para>
    <para>Since the DocBook specification is huge, it is not fully supported. What is supported and what not is described in
        <code>db5-dialect-description-article.*</code>.</para>

  </sect1>

